The paper deals with the problem of detecting and removing backdoor attacks on deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the security implications of such attacks, which makes it relevant to the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The experiments conducted in the paper involve classification of text and images, which suggests that the paper could also be classified under computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the proposed approach involves clustering of neuron activations, which is a technique commonly used in neural network optimization and training, making the paper relevant to the sub-category of neural networks (cs.NE).
